Action For Rural Rejuvenation (ARR) is a program aimed towards improving the overall health and quality of life of the rural poor. It was established by the Isha Foundation  As of 2010, ARR has reached over 4,200 villages and a population of over 7 million people. The city of Columbus in the state of Ohio, United States has felicitated Sadhguru Jaggi Vasudev the founder of ARR for the social programs and activities conducted by ARR.
